Coronavirus guidance is being updated.
Read what you can and cannot do

North Korea has put measures in place to limit the spread of coronavirus (COVID-19).
For information on how to return to the UK from North Korea, see Return to the UK
In response, the North Korean authorities have introduced a series of travel restrictions. Tour operators have reported a government suspension of tourism into North Korea.
All air and train routes into and out of North Korea have been temporarily suspended as of 31 January 2020. If you have existing travel plans you should check with your transport provider before travelling.
Foreigners who have travelled into North Korea from virus-affected countries are subject to a 30 day period of quarantine and medical supervision.
See the TravelHealthPro website for further advice on travel abroad and reducing spread of respiratory viruses during the COVID-19 pandemic.
